Dr. Thomas H. Baker is a Project Leader at the Birlinghoven
Library of Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft in Bonn.  He holds an
MLS from Rutgers University and a Ph.D. in anthropology from
Stanford University, and he taught for two years at the Asian
Institute of Technology in Bangkok.  As a partner in the
EU-funded projects SCHEMAS and CORES, an activity lead in
the DELOS Network of Excellence, and founding head of the
Usage Board of the Dublin Core Metadata Initiative, he is
interested in the development of open standards for metadata
and related registry infrastructures.